text:
Had egg plaster prata with teh tarik.  Teh was great, well balanced tea /milk combination with tinge of sweet tea flavour.
The texture of the prata, was “tough”, not the soft fluffy kind that I would generally enjoy.  However, thumbs up the prata for not greasy at all.  May be back to try their other menu.
I enjoyed the lotong! For me it’s without chilli as it will be too spicy for me. In term of pricing, it is pretty affordable for this location. Will definitely visit here to try out other dishes :))
paprik ayam, nasi goreng pattya taste great and not very spicy. Tissue prata only comes with honey.
This shop has good service and a clean environment. The milk tea is rich and delicious, and the food is also delicious. It is worth a meal here and highly recommended.
Generous portions and tastes not bad. Mee Goreng was decent!
